# Content Editing Rules

## Changelog Files (`src/data/changelog/`)

Every changelog file MUST have all of these frontmatter fields:

```yaml
---
title: "vX.Y.Z - Brief one-line description"
version: "X.Y.Z"              # Semantic version string
publishDate: YYYY-MM-DD       # ISO date (no time)
type: patch                   # ONLY: major | minor | patch | hotfix
downloadUrl: "/downloads/psimonitor-vX.Y.Z.zip"
isLatest: false               # Only ONE file may have true at any time
---
```

Rules:
- Never modify an existing changelog file — only create new ones
- When creating a new release with `isLatest: true`, first update the previous latest to `isLatest: false`
- File naming must be exactly: `vX.Y.Z.md` (e.g., `v1.2.3.md`)
- Body must use H3 sections: `### Changes`, `### Fixed`, `### Known Issues`

## FAQ Files (`src/data/faq/`)

Every FAQ file MUST have:

```yaml
---
question: "The full question text?"
category: installation  # ONLY: installation | trading | billing | technical | general
order: 1               # Integer for sort order within category
---
```

## JSON Data Files (`src/data/*.json`)

- `products.json` — product metadata only, no legal claims
- `pricing.json` — pricing tiers, do NOT change prices without user confirmation
- `features.json` — feature list, use conservative language (see AGENTS.md)
- `compliance.json` — READ ONLY by AI, human edit only

## Prohibited Content in Any File

- Claims of guaranteed financial returns
- "Risk-free" descriptions
- Statistics that imply profit outcomes (e.g., "80% win rate")
- Any language that could be construed as financial advice
